2
00:00:51.469 --> 00:00:52.803
{\an8}EPISODE 1

3
00:00:52.887 --> 00:00:54.430
{\an8}IMPERIAL PRINT

4
00:01:07.318 --> 00:01:08.611
{\an8}You're closing up again?

5
00:01:08.694 --> 00:01:10.905
{\an8}I just have two things left to do!

6
00:01:12.490 --> 00:01:14.074
{\an8}Handle the reprint request yet?

7
00:01:14.158 --> 00:01:16.327
{\an8}Yeah. switched to rough-gloss paper.

8
00:01:16.410 --> 00:01:18.370
{\an8}-Good call! Well done.
-Thanks. man.

9
00:01:20.706 --> 00:01:22.291
-There you are!
-Hi there!

10
00:01:22.374 --> 00:01:26.629
-Come on. guys! Fried chicken. Have some.
-All right! Fried chicken.

11
00:01:26.712 --> 00:01:28.631
-Hey. Hwang!
-Fried chicken. Yes!

12
00:01:29.423 --> 00:01:33.385
<i>-♪ I gave you my heart. my love. my all ♪
-♪ My love. my all ♪</i>

13
00:01:33.469 --> 00:01:36.931
<i>♪ But now you're leaving
Like a stranger ♪</i>

14
00:01:37.014 --> 00:01:40.476
<i>-♪ Take the pain of goodbye with you ♪
-♪ Take the pain of goodbye with you ♪</i>

15
00:01:43.270 --> 00:01:45.314
<i>-♪ You heartless one ♪
-♪ You heartless one ♪</i>

16
00:01:45.397 --> 00:01:47.358
-You made my ears bleed. seriously.
-Listen.

17
00:01:47.441 --> 00:01:49.986
What do you call a big. proud chicken.

18
00:01:50.069 --> 00:01:52.822
like one that's full of itself?
Any idea? Hmm?

19
00:01:52.905 --> 00:01:57.618
Pride chicken!

20
00:01:58.619 --> 00:02:01.247
-Looks good.
-Yeah. pride chicken!

21
00:02:01.330 --> 00:02:03.082
I heard you. sir.

22
00:02:03.999 --> 00:02:06.210
Dude. I thought it was really funny.

23
00:02:06.293 --> 00:02:08.004
-Thanks for the chicken though.
-Oh. man.

24
00:02:08.087 --> 00:02:10.589
Oh. well. Hey. hey. hey. Wait. Hang on.

25
00:02:12.049 --> 00:02:13.592
Looks amazing.

26
00:02:14.844 --> 00:02:16.053
Damn. it's already cold.

27
00:02:20.766 --> 00:02:23.519
Shoot. how did you even see that?
Let me explain...

28
00:02:27.523 --> 00:02:28.941
IMPERIAL PRINT

29
00:02:29.024 --> 00:02:31.944
I got so much done today.
There. finished.

30
00:02:32.695 --> 00:02:34.572
Hey. this... this.

31
00:02:35.197 --> 00:02:37.283
Can't you just deliver this yourself?

32
00:02:38.492 --> 00:02:41.662
I get it.
You don't want to do it. right?

33
00:02:41.745 --> 00:02:43.789
If you were me. would you want to do it?

34
00:02:43.873 --> 00:02:46.458
It's just. it's Chae-bin's birthday...

35
00:02:47.334 --> 00:02:49.003
Wow.

36
00:02:49.086 --> 00:02:51.839
Okay. it's all good. It's nearby.
so I'll do it. It's all right.

37
00:02:51.922 --> 00:02:53.507
Ah. it's Chae-bin's birthday?

38
00:02:54.341 --> 00:02:57.303
-Just go home. I'll do it.
-Oh. no way.

39
00:02:57.386 --> 00:03:00.264
What if you run into Se-na?
That'd be so awkward.

40
00:03:00.347 --> 00:03:01.348
Hey.

41
00:03:02.641 --> 00:03:04.101
What if I go like this?

42
00:03:05.060 --> 00:03:06.353
I won't be recognized.

43
00:03:06.437 --> 00:03:09.523
You think your ex won't recognize you
in that stupid dad hat of yours?

44
00:03:09.607 --> 00:03:11.191
Ah. man.

45
00:03:11.275 --> 00:03:14.111
I wonder if she even knows
that this is your life now.

46
00:03:15.321 --> 00:03:16.488
You sure you wanna do this?

47
00:03:16.572 --> 00:03:18.616
You better go before I change my mind.

48
00:03:18.699 --> 00:03:21.076
-Thanks. man. See you!
-Hey!

49
00:03:34.924 --> 00:03:36.175
{\an8}THE QUEEN OF MELODRAMA

50
00:03:41.472 --> 00:03:42.473
{\an8}15 YEARS AGO

51
00:03:46.101 --> 00:03:47.478
Just get out of here. all right?

52
00:03:47.561 --> 00:03:48.687
I've got to get home.

53
00:03:49.480 --> 00:03:51.023
Mr. Hong.

54
00:03:51.106 --> 00:03:53.984
This is all a misunderstanding.

55
00:03:54.068 --> 00:03:57.696
It's true we met through <i>Sad Waltz</i> and
were seeing each other for a while then.

56
00:03:57.780 --> 00:03:59.990
but I swear we broke up a long time ago!

57
00:04:01.116 --> 00:04:03.869
So. if this dating scandal gets out.
I'll have to drop all of

58
00:04:03.953 --> 00:04:07.456
the commercials. romantic movies
and mini-series I signed on for.

59
00:04:07.539 --> 00:04:10.334
And on top of that. I'll have to pay
huge penalties. so please!

60
00:04:10.417 --> 00:04:11.585
Okay. okay. Listen.

61
00:04:11.669 --> 00:04:14.004
This whole thing
is your problem. isn't it?

62
00:04:14.088 --> 00:04:16.507
Why should we care? I mean.
come on. the proof is right here.

63
00:04:16.590 --> 00:04:18.092
Don't lie to my face.

64
00:04:18.175 --> 00:04:19.718
No. you're wrong.

65
00:04:21.136 --> 00:04:25.224
He was still totally hung up on me
and kept begging to meet. so I gave in.

66
00:04:25.808 --> 00:04:29.645
He said he'd show up at my shoot
if I didn't. and I couldn't risk that.

67
00:04:29.728 --> 00:04:31.605
So I really didn't have a choice.

68
00:04:34.650 --> 00:04:36.860
Say something. Come on. please.

69
00:04:36.944 --> 00:04:40.322
It's true. right?
Tell him that's what happened.

70
00:04:42.032 --> 00:04:43.033
Please.

71
00:04:43.701 --> 00:04:45.119
Oh. come on.

72
00:04:45.202 --> 00:04:47.454
Why are you kneeling?
This is so awkward.

73
00:04:47.538 --> 00:04:50.791
-Will you just get up?
-Sir. that's what happened.

74
00:04:51.667 --> 00:04:52.668
I...

75
00:04:54.169 --> 00:04:55.754
It's true. I threatened her.

76
00:04:56.672 --> 00:04:57.673
Mr. Hong.

77
00:04:59.508 --> 00:05:01.927
-You can't. Please. don't run the story.
-See?

78
00:05:02.011 --> 00:05:05.431
I told you. We really aren't involved.
I swear. it's not true at all.

79
00:05:05.514 --> 00:05:08.767
I promise. Mr. Hong.
Please. you have to believe me.

80
00:05:30.539 --> 00:05:33.292
Aren't they all hotshots?
Why meet in this dump?

81
00:06:03.113 --> 00:06:05.074
-Oh. I'm sorry. ma'am.
-I'm sorry.

82
00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:18.128
Mmm.

83
00:06:19.296 --> 00:06:20.339
Ms. Wi. you made it.

84
00:06:23.801 --> 00:06:25.219
Why are you alone. if I may ask?

85
00:06:25.844 --> 00:06:28.055
-And the congressman?
-I don't think a journalist like you

86
00:06:28.138 --> 00:06:30.516
is on the level to have
a private meeting with him.

87
00:06:33.852 --> 00:06:34.853
Have a seat.

88
00:06:48.867 --> 00:06:53.497
I'll be in the US for about eight months
filming the second season of <i>Save Zone.</i>

89
00:06:54.039 --> 00:06:55.666
-so I guess the timing won't work out.
-Of course.

90
00:06:55.749 --> 00:06:58.043
Time always flies
when we're prepping for a new shoot.

91
00:06:58.127 --> 00:06:59.503
so eight months will feel like nothing.

92
00:06:59.586 --> 00:07:02.840
If I know for sure you're on board.
I'd gladly wait even eight freaking years.

93
00:07:04.466 --> 00:07:06.426
Yeah?

94
00:07:06.510 --> 00:07:08.637
Hello. I'm here to drop off the script.

95
00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:10.556
Hey. Mr. Lim. That was quick. Thanks.

96
00:07:10.639 --> 00:07:12.349
Oh! Why is this all wet?

97
00:07:12.432 --> 00:07:14.017
It-It's raining outside.

98
00:07:14.101 --> 00:07:15.102
All right.

99
00:07:16.854 --> 00:07:17.980
What's this?

100
00:07:18.063 --> 00:07:20.440
The script we had custom-printed for you.

101
00:07:20.524 --> 00:07:22.693
Well. I'll be off. then.

102
00:07:22.776 --> 00:07:24.236
Wait.

103
00:07:25.028 --> 00:07:26.155
Thank you.

104
00:07:30.159 --> 00:07:31.285
This print looks good.

105
00:07:31.368 --> 00:07:33.078
You think so?

106
00:07:33.162 --> 00:07:36.123
It's a special edition we had
custom ordered just for you!

107
00:07:38.333 --> 00:07:39.501
Sir!

108
00:07:45.048 --> 00:07:46.466
So let me ask you something.

109
00:07:46.967 --> 00:07:49.970
Does Mr. Ha Gee-wan hire aides
just to use them as a shield?

110
00:07:50.053 --> 00:07:53.974
Are you saying he really has nothing to do
with Cheongwon City's redevelopment?

111
00:07:54.057 --> 00:07:57.102
That it was just his aide who
took all that money and spent it?

112
00:07:57.186 --> 00:08:00.189
Yeah. I know why you're upset.
The nerve of that guy. right?

113
00:08:00.272 --> 00:08:01.690
Mr. Woo Young-suk.

114
00:08:02.900 --> 00:08:04.860
I was supposed to meet him tomorrow.

115
00:08:05.736 --> 00:08:07.613
So how come he's dead right now?

116
00:08:07.696 --> 00:08:10.699
<i>Breaking news. This morning
at a private parking lot in Seoul.</i>

117
00:08:10.782 --> 00:08:12.701
<i>Woo. an aide to congressman Ha Gee-wan.</i>

118
00:08:12.784 --> 00:08:16.079
<i>who proposed a special law tied to
the Cheongwon City redevelopment project.</i>

119
00:08:16.163 --> 00:08:17.372
<i>was found dead.</i>

120
00:08:17.456 --> 00:08:20.000
<i>Charcoal briquettes and a note.
believed to be a suicide letter.</i>

121
00:08:20.083 --> 00:08:22.502
<i>were also discovered at the scene.</i>

122
00:08:22.586 --> 00:08:26.048
Look. Ms. Wi. I guess you're upset
about missing the exclusive.

123
00:08:26.131 --> 00:08:27.925
young and passionate
journalist that you are.

124
00:08:28.008 --> 00:08:30.302
but that's just a fact. okay?

125
00:08:30.385 --> 00:08:33.931
You think I'm upset? Are you kidding?

126
00:08:34.514 --> 00:08:37.434
Well. even Mr. Woo's family
doesn't want to make this a big deal.

127
00:08:37.517 --> 00:08:40.520
So if you keep poking around.
a lot of people are going to get hurt.

128
00:08:40.604 --> 00:08:43.232
I hope we have an understanding. Ms. Wi.

129
00:08:44.066 --> 00:08:45.067
Open it.

130
00:08:49.696 --> 00:08:51.490
A journalist needs to be mobile.

131
00:08:53.367 --> 00:08:54.785
That should be enough for a decent SUV.

132
00:08:54.868 --> 00:08:56.787
Maybe even
with all the bells and whistles.

133
00:08:58.121 --> 00:08:59.623
Now get the hell out.

134
00:09:17.266 --> 00:09:18.433
What are you doing?

135
00:09:32.030 --> 00:09:34.032
Thanks to you. I have learned so much.

136
00:09:34.950 --> 00:09:36.576
This pays for the lesson.

137
00:09:44.710 --> 00:09:46.086
Seriously?

138
00:09:46.169 --> 00:09:47.963
Is it something to be embarrassed about?

139
00:09:48.505 --> 00:09:51.300
What's so embarrassing
that I had to throw on this stupid hat?

140
00:10:02.936 --> 00:10:04.730
I had a feeling it was you.

141
00:10:05.564 --> 00:10:06.565
It's been a while.

142
00:10:07.399 --> 00:10:09.318
Gotta say. you haven't changed much.

143
00:10:13.405 --> 00:10:14.698
You haven't changed one bit.

144
00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:19.077
So why did you come here?
I'd like to know.

145
00:10:20.162 --> 00:10:22.247
You knew I'd be here tonight.

146
00:10:22.331 --> 00:10:23.707
so you shouldn't have come.

147
00:10:25.417 --> 00:10:28.795
You thought I'd feel bad or guilty.
seeing you like that? That what happened?

148
00:10:28.879 --> 00:10:31.048
-What?
-Or what? Life's that hard?

149
00:10:31.131 --> 00:10:32.299
Struggling to survive?

150
00:10:43.477 --> 00:10:45.270
I think I'll just ignore that.

151
00:10:49.232 --> 00:10:50.650
Take care.

152
00:11:12.798 --> 00:11:14.883
<i>You knew I'd be here tonight.</i>

153
00:11:15.550 --> 00:11:17.427
<i>so you shouldn't have come.</i>

154
00:11:24.893 --> 00:11:29.398
{\an8}15 YEARS AGO

155
00:11:46.957 --> 00:11:47.958
And cut!

156
00:11:57.843 --> 00:11:59.428
Give me that.

157
00:12:01.972 --> 00:12:03.765
Hey. Don't.

158
00:12:03.849 --> 00:12:05.142
I got it.

159
00:12:12.107 --> 00:12:13.567
Hmm?

160
00:12:13.650 --> 00:12:14.901
Who are you?

161
00:12:15.485 --> 00:12:17.529
Oh. my God!

162
00:12:17.612 --> 00:12:18.864
-What the...
-You scared me.

163
00:12:18.947 --> 00:12:20.365
-Who are you?
-Who are you?

164
00:12:21.032 --> 00:12:22.284
What?

165
00:12:22.367 --> 00:12:23.994
I almost died. How did you get in the car?

166
00:12:24.077 --> 00:12:26.497
-What car? What are you talking about?
-You're freaking me out.

167
00:12:26.580 --> 00:12:28.874
Yes. hello. I think I'm being
kidnapped right now.

168
00:12:28.957 --> 00:12:31.668
What is she talking about?
What do you mean kidnapped? Hey!

169
00:12:31.751 --> 00:12:33.253
-Watch out! Don't open that door!
-Yes.

170
00:12:33.336 --> 00:12:35.005
I think we're driving
over a bridge right now.

171
00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:37.424
Excuse me. What is the bridge
we're on now?

172
00:12:38.216 --> 00:12:39.551
It's the Yeongdong Bridge!

173
00:12:39.634 --> 00:12:40.969
Yeongdong Bridge! It's the Yeongdong...

174
00:12:41.052 --> 00:12:43.722
-Please come to the Yeongdong Bridge now!
-What? Is this woman crazy?

175
00:12:43.805 --> 00:12:45.348
-Yeongdong Bridge.
-Oh. shit.

176
00:12:45.432 --> 00:12:47.100
It's a tall bridge. You can't miss it.

177
00:12:47.767 --> 00:12:49.686
A RELIABLE POLICE FORCE.
A SAFE NATION

178
00:12:49.769 --> 00:12:53.315
All right. Since you both came
in voluntarily over this misunderstanding.

179
00:12:53.398 --> 00:12:56.026
we'll take a look
at the dashcam footage together.

180
00:12:58.028 --> 00:12:59.029
Here. look.

181
00:13:11.750 --> 00:13:13.335
Great. Seriously.

182
00:13:13.418 --> 00:13:15.712
All right. This is the footage
from the front camera.

183
00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:18.048
Okay. next one.

184
00:13:20.425 --> 00:13:22.469
-Unbelievable.
<i>-I feel like death.</i>

185
00:13:22.552 --> 00:13:24.971
Look at the footage. detective.
I'm not the one lying.

186
00:13:25.055 --> 00:13:27.182
This confirms she got into my car
on her own. right?

187
00:13:27.265 --> 00:13:29.601
-So I didn't do anything wrong.
-Let's keep watching.

188
00:13:29.684 --> 00:13:33.021
I mean. who knows? He could've known
I was in the car all along.

189
00:13:33.772 --> 00:13:36.316
Wow.
what's wrong with you. lady?

190
00:13:37.943 --> 00:13:40.195
Okay. fine. Go ahead. hit play.
Let's keep watching.

191
00:13:40.278 --> 00:13:41.404
All right. sure.

192
00:13:42.697 --> 00:13:44.324
<i>That bitch. Seriously.</i>

193
00:13:47.410 --> 00:13:48.828
<i>"You shouldn't have come"?</i>

194
00:13:49.579 --> 00:13:52.874
-No. That... By "that bitch." I meant...
-<i>I mean. who does she think she is?</i>

195
00:13:52.958 --> 00:13:54.626
<i>I swear.</i>

196
00:13:54.709 --> 00:13:57.128
<i>Obviously I lied when I said
she hadn't changed one bit.</i>

197
00:13:57.212 --> 00:14:00.048
Her face is all sagging now.
with wrinkles around her damn eyes.

198
00:14:01.550 --> 00:14:05.345
And how is it that your acting
hasn't shown any improvement at all?

199
00:14:05.929 --> 00:14:08.306
You haven't gotten any better.
Not one bit.

200
00:14:08.390 --> 00:14:10.517
No progress. None!

201
00:14:11.268 --> 00:14:15.355
That same long straight hair. same
lousy acting. the exact same expression.

202
00:14:15.438 --> 00:14:17.357
How boring! I'm sick of it!

203
00:14:17.440 --> 00:14:20.694
<i>I'm so freaking sick of it! So lame!</i>
<i>It's pathetic!</i>

204
00:14:22.404 --> 00:14:23.780
<i>Who are you?</i>

205
00:14:29.077 --> 00:14:30.496
-See. that was...
-Well I guess

206
00:14:30.579 --> 00:14:33.540
you were just really angry. yeah?

207
00:14:34.124 --> 00:14:36.626
Anyhow. that being said. you two
are good now. aren't you?

208
00:14:36.710 --> 00:14:38.753
Oh... Uh...

209
00:14:39.421 --> 00:14:40.589
Um. I'm...

210
00:14:42.507 --> 00:14:44.718
I'm... I'm really sorry.

211
00:14:46.011 --> 00:14:47.637
If you're sorry. then we're fine.

212
00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:50.849
I can't believe you said
I kidnapped you. though...

213
00:14:51.725 --> 00:14:53.560
Oh. my God. It's like...

214
00:14:53.643 --> 00:14:54.894
I know. right?

215
00:14:54.978 --> 00:14:57.772
An innocent man died because of me.

216
00:14:58.732 --> 00:15:00.275
And you're here because of me.

217
00:15:03.903 --> 00:15:06.114
I don't know what the hell
is wrong with me.

218
00:15:06.197 --> 00:15:08.408
So. Dete...

219
00:15:08.491 --> 00:15:10.744
You're so dumb! Such an idiot!

220
00:15:14.164 --> 00:15:18.460
Detective. just arrest me now. Please.
someone like me deserves to be arrested.

221
00:15:18.543 --> 00:15:22.464
If I keep wandering around like this.
I don't know what stupid thing I'll do.

222
00:15:22.547 --> 00:15:23.798
I'd rather just be put in jail.

223
00:15:23.882 --> 00:15:26.635
Please. please.
Oh. please just put me in jail!

224
00:15:26.718 --> 00:15:28.595
Please. just lock me up. Take me away now.

225
00:15:28.678 --> 00:15:30.556
-I can't take it anymore.
-She's just drunk and rambling.

226
00:15:30.639 --> 00:15:31.973
So. I'm going home now. okay?

227
00:15:32.057 --> 00:15:34.351
I'm free to go. right?

228
00:15:36.519 --> 00:15:38.104
Thank you. sir. Bye.

229
00:15:38.855 --> 00:15:43.026
Just put me in jail. please.
Please.

230
00:16:09.427 --> 00:16:10.929
Drink that. It'll help you sober up.

231
00:16:11.971 --> 00:16:13.932
Stay out of other people's cars.

232
00:16:15.183 --> 00:16:17.894
Hey. don't you know
it's a scary place out there?

233
00:16:18.645 --> 00:16:21.523
Honestly. lady. you're really lucky
that it was my car.

234
00:16:23.733 --> 00:16:24.734
Thanks a lot.

235
00:16:28.446 --> 00:16:30.615
You look like you have an office job.

236
00:16:31.282 --> 00:16:34.494
So I really don't see why you
drink so much in the first place.

237
00:16:35.328 --> 00:16:37.163
There's one thing I know for sure.

238
00:16:37.247 --> 00:16:40.041
Even when bad things happen.
more often than not. it's not your fault.

239
00:16:40.125 --> 00:16:43.128
So stop beating yourself up
and just move forward.

240
00:16:43.837 --> 00:16:45.088
Because you need to succeed...

241
00:16:46.089 --> 00:16:48.508
<i>Or what? Life's that hard?
Struggling to survive?</i>

242
00:16:50.301 --> 00:16:52.053
Or people will think less of you.

243
00:16:53.888 --> 00:16:56.391
Hold on just a minute.

244
00:17:01.229 --> 00:17:03.565
THANK YOU EUNSEONGILBO

245
00:17:05.859 --> 00:17:08.361
Uh. if you ever
need my help with anything.

246
00:17:08.945 --> 00:17:10.321
feel free to get in touch.

247
00:17:21.374 --> 00:17:23.084
All right. sure.

248
00:17:23.168 --> 00:17:24.627
Come on. don't give me that look.

249
00:17:25.253 --> 00:17:27.213
You're creeping me out.

250
00:17:28.715 --> 00:17:30.467
Anyway. I'm off. Bye-bye.

251
00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:41.204
{\an8}<i>Mr. Woo Young-suk.
I was supposed to meet him tomorrow.</i>

252
00:18:41.996 --> 00:18:43.998
<i>So how come he's dead right now?</i>

253
00:19:10.191 --> 00:19:11.671
GWON SE-NA NAMED MUSE
FOR LUXURY BRAND

254
00:19:13.444 --> 00:19:15.488
GWON SE-NA'S SAVE ZONE
IS A GLOBAL HIT

255
00:19:37.302 --> 00:19:38.386
Hello.

256
00:19:39.345 --> 00:19:40.388
Yes? Hello.

257
00:19:40.471 --> 00:19:42.390
I had a screenplay
printed here a while ago.

258
00:19:42.473 --> 00:19:45.476
and I just noticed
there's a small problem with it.

259
00:19:46.060 --> 00:19:47.061
I need to show you.

260
00:19:48.980 --> 00:19:49.981
What kind?

261
00:19:50.565 --> 00:19:51.691
GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU

262
00:19:53.359 --> 00:19:54.903
Ah. this.

263
00:19:56.279 --> 00:19:58.406
I believe it was Mr. Hwang
who took care of this.

264
00:19:58.489 --> 00:20:02.285
I heard it's an indie film.
a college graduation project.

265
00:20:02.368 --> 00:20:04.829
so we didn't take any profit.
just cover the cost.

266
00:20:04.913 --> 00:20:06.122
-Is that right?
-That's right.

267
00:20:06.205 --> 00:20:08.541
He was kind enough
to offer a discount for printing it.

268
00:20:08.625 --> 00:20:10.085
And even though the schedule was tight.

269
00:20:10.168 --> 00:20:12.003
he still managed to meet
every single deadline

270
00:20:12.086 --> 00:20:13.880
and handled more than
ten revisions for the cover.

271
00:20:13.963 --> 00:20:15.131
Thanks a lot for that.

272
00:20:15.214 --> 00:20:16.382
Ah. yeah.

273
00:20:16.466 --> 00:20:18.343
Mr. Hwang went out of his way for you.

274
00:20:18.426 --> 00:20:19.427
He came through for sure.

275
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:21.512
I'm genuinely grateful
for everything he did.

276
00:20:21.596 --> 00:20:25.141
but this is business. and it didn't feel
right to just ignore all the mistakes.

277
00:20:27.101 --> 00:20:29.979
If you're really grateful.
you can look past the little things.

278
00:20:30.063 --> 00:20:32.523
But this is my first feature.
so with all due respect.

279
00:20:32.607 --> 00:20:34.817
I don't think I can just let them slide.

280
00:20:41.908 --> 00:20:43.868
Fair enough. all right.
What are the mistakes?

281
00:20:44.494 --> 00:20:45.703
Yeah. hold on.

282
00:20:45.787 --> 00:20:48.748
Well. first. the best boy electric's name
is Na Yun-seon.

283
00:20:48.831 --> 00:20:51.125
although right here.
it's written as "Na Un-seon."

284
00:20:51.209 --> 00:20:53.878
Also the cover has a slight reddish tint.
but I was actually hoping

285
00:20:53.962 --> 00:20:57.590
for something softer
and a little more neutral in tone.

286
00:20:57.674 --> 00:20:59.926
Overall. the left/right balance is off.

287
00:21:00.009 --> 00:21:02.387
There's about a 2 mm difference
between the sides. See this?

288
00:21:02.470 --> 00:21:04.973
I asked him to use Hamchorong Batang
Extended Bold as the font.

289
00:21:05.056 --> 00:21:06.349
but he used Extended Non-bold.

290
00:21:06.933 --> 00:21:09.602
Could you please switch it
to Hamchorong Batang Extended Bold?

291
00:21:13.439 --> 00:21:15.191
-That's it? Are you done?
-Yeah.

292
00:21:16.567 --> 00:21:18.153
Didn't you mention
your timeline was tight?

293
00:21:18.236 --> 00:21:21.948
True. I'm sorry to spring this on you.
but I need it done by tomorrow.

294
00:21:23.116 --> 00:21:25.827
I swear. that place is so cool.

295
00:21:28.538 --> 00:21:30.039
No. not you. him.

296
00:21:32.208 --> 00:21:33.501
What now?

297
00:21:33.584 --> 00:21:36.462
Hamchorong Batang Bold is what he needed.

298
00:21:37.171 --> 00:21:38.172
Bold.

299
00:21:41.509 --> 00:21:44.262
All right. see you.

300
00:21:45.930 --> 00:21:48.850
That dude's worse
than the guys at the TV station.

301
00:21:48.933 --> 00:21:50.560
I thought you were gonna punch him.

302
00:21:50.643 --> 00:21:53.021
That's why I called you over.
I was worried I might.

303
00:21:53.104 --> 00:21:54.272
It was definitely a close call.

304
00:21:54.355 --> 00:21:56.983
Glad you didn't. That jerk
would've only made you hurt your hand.

305
00:22:01.404 --> 00:22:02.405
Oh. hey!

306
00:22:03.114 --> 00:22:05.554
-See you later.
-Why is this font guy still here?

307
00:22:06.784 --> 00:22:09.495
-Man. that guy is weird as hell.
-Why is he doing this to us?

308
00:22:09.579 --> 00:22:10.747
Should I sprinkle some salt?

309
00:22:10.830 --> 00:22:12.457
Maybe that'll chase his creepy vibe away.

310
00:22:12.540 --> 00:22:13.541
Seriously.

311
00:22:13.624 --> 00:22:15.293
Why is he familiar?

312
00:22:17.003 --> 00:22:18.713
"<i>Good Detective Kang Pil-go</i>"?

313
00:22:19.297 --> 00:22:22.091
Seriously. that's a weird title.
Really freakin' weird.

314
00:22:37.315 --> 00:22:39.817
That jerk.

315
00:22:41.986 --> 00:22:42.987
He's a genius.

316
00:22:57.251 --> 00:22:59.504
Hey! What the hell?

317
00:23:01.964 --> 00:23:04.342
Could you please switch it
to Hamchorong Batang Extended Bold?

318
00:23:04.425 --> 00:23:07.637
Hamchorong? You... Have you lost it?

319
00:23:07.720 --> 00:23:09.639
You scared the hell out of me.

320
00:23:09.722 --> 00:23:11.015
I remember you now.

321
00:23:13.017 --> 00:23:14.185
Spit it out.

322
00:23:14.268 --> 00:23:17.146
I was sure
I'd seen you somewhere.

323
00:23:17.230 --> 00:23:19.190
but I couldn't remember until I got home.

324
00:23:19.273 --> 00:23:21.276
I kept racking my brain while eating.
walking my dog.

325
00:23:21.359 --> 00:23:23.528
even taking out the trash.
though nothing came to me.

326
00:23:23.611 --> 00:23:26.531
I thought I was gonna lose my mind.
then as soon as I went to bed.

327
00:23:26.614 --> 00:23:27.824
I knew who you were.

328
00:23:27.907 --> 00:23:29.992
You were in the movie <i>Sad Waltz</i>.

329
00:23:30.076 --> 00:23:31.994
You're an actor!

330
00:23:33.454 --> 00:23:36.041
Did you go home and come all the way
back here just to tell me that?

331
00:23:36.124 --> 00:23:37.125
Oh. no.

332
00:23:37.792 --> 00:23:38.876
I'm here to cast you.

333
00:23:41.546 --> 00:23:42.880
Is that right?

334
00:23:42.964 --> 00:23:46.217
I'd like you to be in my film.
<i>Good Detective Kang Pil-go.</i>

335
00:23:46.300 --> 00:23:49.387
as the main character.
the good detective. Kang Pil-go.

336
00:24:00.273 --> 00:24:02.817
Come on. Let's go. What the...

337
00:24:05.069 --> 00:24:06.571
GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU

338
00:24:06.654 --> 00:24:08.614
Get in. get in.

339
00:24:11.993 --> 00:24:14.537
Come on. move aside.
Move. we're busy. Come on.

340
00:24:14.620 --> 00:24:16.372
We're busy. man. damn it. Come on. move!

341
00:24:16.455 --> 00:24:18.083
I don't have time for this!

342
00:24:18.166 --> 00:24:20.376
So basically. the color didn't hold?

343
00:24:20.960 --> 00:24:24.088
...but he figures it all out.

344
00:24:24.172 --> 00:24:25.173
Come over.

345
00:24:25.256 --> 00:24:27.925
Oh. I see. right.
Then we should reprint it for you.

346
00:24:28.009 --> 00:24:29.177
Yeah. for sure.

347
00:24:37.185 --> 00:24:38.978
Ah. shit! You scared me.

348
00:24:39.061 --> 00:24:41.230
Leading Man. Heading home now?

349
00:24:41.814 --> 00:24:44.775
Seriously?
Why the hell are you still here?

350
00:24:44.859 --> 00:24:46.986
-Come on. go home.
-I'm going. I wanted to give you this.

351
00:24:47.069 --> 00:24:48.237
Just go. man. Come on. leave.

352
00:24:48.321 --> 00:24:49.906
Just this once? Would you please consider?

353
00:24:49.989 --> 00:24:52.117
I already told you I wasn't interested.
Get out of here.

354
00:24:52.200 --> 00:24:53.826
You didn't have to lock yourself in.

355
00:24:53.910 --> 00:24:55.077
This is harassment.

356
00:24:55.161 --> 00:24:57.455
-I won't change my mind. Get out!
-Help me this one time. please?

357
00:24:58.956 --> 00:25:00.124
Leading Man.

358
00:25:00.208 --> 00:25:02.376
Seriously?

359
00:25:02.460 --> 00:25:04.545
-He's driving me nuts.
-Leading Man. come on.

360
00:25:04.629 --> 00:25:07.632
Cut this shit out! Stop calling me
Leading Man. Get out of here now. okay?

361
00:25:07.715 --> 00:25:10.551
Look. Mr. Lim.
I really want you to star in my movie.

362
00:25:10.635 --> 00:25:13.262
Your school
is one of the best. right?

363
00:25:13.346 --> 00:25:15.556
Must be full of actors.
Why do you need me to do it?

364
00:25:15.640 --> 00:25:17.517
What makes you think
you can trust me with that role?

365
00:25:17.600 --> 00:25:21.437
Hey! I get it's just a graduation project.
but you don't want it to fail.

366
00:25:21.520 --> 00:25:23.773
I'm doing this to make it successful.

367
00:25:23.856 --> 00:25:25.775
Okay. fine.

368
00:25:27.276 --> 00:25:28.819
I'm really curious too.

369
00:25:28.903 --> 00:25:31.781
So why do you want me?
Why me for that tough detective?

370
00:25:31.864 --> 00:25:34.450
Because I know you'll do a great job.

371
00:25:34.533 --> 00:25:37.370
I'm not good with words. so it's tough
to explain. but I'm sure you get my point.

372
00:25:37.453 --> 00:25:40.498
It won't fail. If you just give me
a chance. I know we can pull it off.

373
00:25:40.581 --> 00:25:41.874
I know we'll make it. sir.

374
00:25:43.209 --> 00:25:45.670
There's so many chase and fight scenes
one after another.

375
00:25:45.753 --> 00:25:47.380
But. hey. I can't fight!

376
00:25:47.463 --> 00:25:50.841
I've got a pacifist's DNA.
It's in my bones. in every part of me.

377
00:25:50.925 --> 00:25:52.093
I'm busy. Just get out of here.

378
00:25:52.176 --> 00:25:54.512
Go. Just go.

379
00:25:54.595 --> 00:25:57.139
Whoa! Come on. wait.
Don't throw it around like that.

380
00:25:57.223 --> 00:25:58.266
Read it carefully.

381
00:25:58.349 --> 00:26:00.685
Ah. Mr. Hwang.
Don't drink too much.

382
00:26:00.768 --> 00:26:03.271
Don't worry. I'm fine. Thank you.

383
00:26:07.108 --> 00:26:09.944
Come on. man. Just do it already.

384
00:26:10.027 --> 00:26:11.988
You're being so difficult.

385
00:26:12.071 --> 00:26:16.242
I mean. who'd watch an indie film directed
by a college student anyway? God's sake.

386
00:26:16.325 --> 00:26:18.077
What if someone I know actually sees it?

387
00:26:18.160 --> 00:26:19.412
I'd just die of embarrassment.

388
00:26:20.204 --> 00:26:24.125
Plus. if no one's going to watch it.
why bother making it in the first place?

389
00:26:27.086 --> 00:26:28.713
See. I read it too. all right?

390
00:26:29.505 --> 00:26:32.591
And. wow! That story's one in a million.

391
00:26:32.675 --> 00:26:35.678
Look. an experienced director
or not. who cares?

392
00:26:35.761 --> 00:26:38.472
It's definitely the kind of story
that. like. fires you up.

393
00:26:38.556 --> 00:26:40.683
Come on. you know I'm right. Don't you?

394
00:26:42.101 --> 00:26:43.102
Yeah.

395
00:26:49.317 --> 00:26:53.112
Hey. When I was doing stage plays
and got recruited by the agency.

396
00:26:53.779 --> 00:26:55.740
you were the first manager that I had.

397
00:26:55.823 --> 00:26:56.907
Yeah.

398
00:26:56.991 --> 00:26:58.326
What was I like back then?

399
00:26:59.827 --> 00:27:00.953
You?

400
00:27:01.537 --> 00:27:02.538
You were

401
00:27:03.581 --> 00:27:04.582
different.

402
00:27:07.126 --> 00:27:09.337
I thought you had the potential
to make it to the top.

403
00:27:09.420 --> 00:27:11.756
You're bluffing. man.

404
00:27:13.716 --> 00:27:17.470
If only
you never dated Gwon Se-na.

405
00:27:17.553 --> 00:27:19.638
you wouldn't be in this mess now.

406
00:27:20.639 --> 00:27:24.060
That heartless. ungrateful brat.

407
00:27:24.810 --> 00:27:27.021
Dude. you broke up with her
for her own good.

408
00:27:27.104 --> 00:27:31.484
So she should be grateful.
but instead she betrayed you to save face.

409
00:27:33.235 --> 00:27:35.363
What's up with that look. man?

410
00:27:35.446 --> 00:27:37.907
No way are you thinking this indie film
could suddenly turn you

411
00:27:37.990 --> 00:27:41.494
into some kinda world-famous movie star
or something. Seriously? Come on.

412
00:27:41.577 --> 00:27:42.953
I wasn't thinking that!

413
00:27:44.080 --> 00:27:45.915
-No need to scream at me.
-Why would you say that?

414
00:27:45.998 --> 00:27:48.250
Why are you getting
so worked up?

415
00:27:50.795 --> 00:27:52.880
Hey. It's all right.

416
00:27:52.963 --> 00:27:56.384
The two of us started the print shop
with nothing. but business is stable now.

417
00:27:56.467 --> 00:27:57.718
Things are pretty good.

418
00:27:58.511 --> 00:28:01.597
Even people who make less than you
are buying new cars and going golfing.

419
00:28:01.680 --> 00:28:04.600
They're living it up. What about you?
What do you do for yourself?

420
00:28:05.518 --> 00:28:06.644
Hey. come on.

421
00:28:06.727 --> 00:28:09.855
Just think of it as a hobby.
Something fun. no pressure.

422
00:28:09.939 --> 00:28:13.150
It's okay to do what you want
every now and then. Am I wrong?

423
00:28:13.984 --> 00:28:16.237
Don't worry about the print shop. okay?

424
00:28:16.320 --> 00:28:17.321
I've got it covered.

425
00:28:18.072 --> 00:28:19.365
Imperial Print!

426
00:28:36.424 --> 00:28:38.592
MR. LEADING MAN.
I'll ASK YOU ONE LAST TIME.

427
00:28:38.676 --> 00:28:41.637
PLEASE BE IN MY MOVIE. IF YOU
TURN ME DOWN AGAIN. I'll STOP.

428
00:28:41.720 --> 00:28:44.598
BUT I URGE THAT YOU CONSIDER IT
WITH A POSITIVE MIND-SET.

429
00:28:57.903 --> 00:28:59.864
{\an8}<i>Are you gonna pay me?</i>

430
00:29:05.327 --> 00:29:08.581
"He spins the handcuffs and
swiftly fastens them on to X's wrists."

431
00:29:10.791 --> 00:29:13.627
"They say you can't really fix people.

432
00:29:14.545 --> 00:29:17.673
but...
...I know that I can."

433
00:29:18.466 --> 00:29:22.386
"Then he stretches out
flat on the floor. right next to X."

434
00:29:22.470 --> 00:29:25.389
Okay. we'll wrap up here.
That's it for today's table read.

435
00:29:25.890 --> 00:29:27.330
Good work today.

436
00:29:27.975 --> 00:29:29.643
Good work. everyone.

437
00:29:29.727 --> 00:29:32.480
Oh. good job.
Good job. everyone. Good job.

438
00:29:33.272 --> 00:29:34.565
-Well done.
-Thank you.

439
00:29:34.648 --> 00:29:37.610
Can I talk to you for a minute?

440
00:29:37.693 --> 00:29:39.570
-Sure.
-He's so good in the role.

441
00:29:39.653 --> 00:29:41.173
I can't wait to see what he does next.

442
00:29:59.840 --> 00:30:03.719
I went a little overboard
earlier. didn't I?

443
00:30:06.472 --> 00:30:08.224
-Hyeon-jun.
-Mm-hmm?

444
00:30:08.307 --> 00:30:10.435
What I'm about to say
is entirely for the sake of our movie.

445
00:30:10.518 --> 00:30:14.188
and I just want to make it clear I'm not
trying to teach or lecture you at all.

446
00:30:14.271 --> 00:30:17.066
Oh yeah. of course. Just tell me already.

447
00:30:17.149 --> 00:30:19.735
You can talk openly.
Don't worry. Go ahead.

448
00:30:19.818 --> 00:30:23.447
Before that. I think we should first
decide how to address each other.

449
00:30:23.531 --> 00:30:25.324
To show respect for our roles.

450
00:30:25.407 --> 00:30:29.203
Okay. Respect. Respect.

451
00:30:30.454 --> 00:30:31.956
You're right. Let's do that.

452
00:30:33.666 --> 00:30:35.709
Sounds good. Director.

453
00:30:36.835 --> 00:30:40.673
So. Hyeon-jun. how would you analyze
or describe your character?

454
00:30:40.756 --> 00:30:43.008
Mmm. well.

455
00:30:43.092 --> 00:30:46.387
he's the type who thinks a good beating
fixes bad guys. you know?

456
00:30:46.470 --> 00:30:50.516
Plus. he also definitely
has that rough. thug mentality.

457
00:30:50.599 --> 00:30:52.768
-Mmm.
-That's what I think.

458
00:30:52.851 --> 00:30:54.353
Director.

459
00:30:55.020 --> 00:30:58.440
So what do you think about the idea
of punishing violence with more violence?

460
00:30:58.524 --> 00:31:02.444
Well. um. it kinda depends
on how serious the violence is though.

461
00:31:02.528 --> 00:31:04.989
Hmm? Case by case. right?

462
00:31:05.072 --> 00:31:06.699
So it all depends on the situation then?

463
00:31:06.782 --> 00:31:09.285
Mmm. mm-hmm!

464
00:31:10.327 --> 00:31:12.913
Right. I can really see that come through
in your performance.

465
00:31:12.997 --> 00:31:14.624
You're not sure if this is right or wrong.

466
00:31:14.707 --> 00:31:18.085
but you're trying to make all the punching
and beating feel as natural as possible.

467
00:31:18.168 --> 00:31:19.545
That's how it comes across.

468
00:31:19.628 --> 00:31:21.422
This guy values fists over the law. Why?

469
00:31:21.505 --> 00:31:25.718
Everything he went through as a kid helped
shape his own unshakable set of values.

470
00:31:25.801 --> 00:31:27.928
So he doesn't feel guilty
when he beats up bad guys.

471
00:31:28.012 --> 00:31:29.263
For this character to be authentic.

472
00:31:29.346 --> 00:31:32.975
he needs to truly believe that his way
is the right way without a doubt.

473
00:31:33.058 --> 00:31:35.227
You need to become one with the character.

474
00:31:35.311 --> 00:31:37.062
Huh?

475
00:31:41.317 --> 00:31:42.318
Yeah.

476
00:31:42.401 --> 00:31:43.902
{\an8}GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU

477
00:31:46.071 --> 00:31:47.740
{\an8}Hey. what are you doing?

478
00:31:48.282 --> 00:31:49.908
Come on. man. we're swamped today.

479
00:31:49.992 --> 00:31:51.785
-Drop off the orders.
-Oh. yeah. okay.

480
00:31:56.832 --> 00:31:59.668
They say you can't really fix people.
but I know I can.

481
00:31:59.752 --> 00:32:01.420
But I can. I can do it.

482
00:32:01.503 --> 00:32:03.505
But I can! I know I can!

483
00:32:03.589 --> 00:32:05.382
I can do it!

484
00:32:05.466 --> 00:32:07.509
I can!

485
00:32:07.593 --> 00:32:09.470
Stop right there!

486
00:32:09.553 --> 00:32:13.098
But I can. I can.

487
00:32:29.239 --> 00:32:30.240
"Stop right there!"

488
00:32:31.617 --> 00:32:32.618
Stop.

489
00:32:34.370 --> 00:32:36.622
Hey. you. Stop right there!

490
00:32:50.344 --> 00:32:52.096
Cut!

491
00:32:55.265 --> 00:32:57.184
He's freaking crazy. right?

492
00:32:58.310 --> 00:33:00.521
My God. three days for one chase scene?

493
00:33:03.440 --> 00:33:05.025
Two and a half. in fact.

494
00:33:06.026 --> 00:33:08.362
All we see on camera
is that you're completely wiped out.

495
00:33:08.445 --> 00:33:09.738
ready to pass out.

496
00:33:10.781 --> 00:33:12.616
Isn't that natural?

497
00:33:12.700 --> 00:33:16.161
I mean. Kang Pil-go
would also be exhausted. right?

498
00:33:16.245 --> 00:33:18.539
Hell no. It's brutal. sure.
but you gotta show grit.

499
00:33:18.622 --> 00:33:22.543
that determination
to make that bastard pay no matter what.

500
00:33:22.626 --> 00:33:24.586
Mm-hmm? Again. from the top.

501
00:33:32.511 --> 00:33:34.972
All right. ready? Action!

502
00:33:37.474 --> 00:33:39.226
All right. cut. cut. cut!

503
00:33:39.309 --> 00:33:41.186
Action!

504
00:33:41.270 --> 00:33:42.563
Cut. cut. cut. cut!

505
00:33:42.646 --> 00:33:43.647
Action!

506
00:33:44.982 --> 00:33:46.191
You all right?

507
00:33:47.860 --> 00:33:49.153
Are you all right?

508
00:33:49.236 --> 00:33:51.071
-Yeah. yeah. thanks.
-Don't stop.

509
00:33:51.155 --> 00:33:52.531
If I don't call "cut." keep going.

510
00:33:52.614 --> 00:33:54.450
Just let it play out.

511
00:33:57.244 --> 00:33:58.245
Come on.

512
00:33:59.371 --> 00:34:01.331
All right.
let's get right back into it.

513
00:34:01.415 --> 00:34:03.500
Okay. ready? Action.

514
00:34:10.883 --> 00:34:13.469
-Aw. shit. Damn.
-Cut.

515
00:34:17.806 --> 00:34:19.933
Hyeon-jun. one more take. Right away.

516
00:34:21.393 --> 00:34:24.271
That little snake.

517
00:34:27.983 --> 00:34:29.568
Ready? Action!

518
00:34:32.362 --> 00:34:35.032
-What?
-Cut.

519
00:34:35.115 --> 00:34:36.867
What the hell?

520
00:34:40.746 --> 00:34:42.331
We're done for the day. Thanks.

521
00:34:42.414 --> 00:34:44.750
-Thanks.
-You can wrap it up.

522
00:34:51.799 --> 00:34:53.383
Let's call it a day for the shoot.

523
00:34:55.886 --> 00:34:58.972
Huh. but we're not done yet.

524
00:35:00.349 --> 00:35:03.310
It seems like you haven't had enough time
to fully analyze your character.

525
00:35:03.393 --> 00:35:06.772
so let's call it a day
and reshoot the scenes another time.

526
00:35:07.606 --> 00:35:08.733
-Pack up. That's a wrap.
-Huh?

527
00:35:08.816 --> 00:35:10.818
Hey. h-hey. hey. hey! No. wait. Come on.

528
00:35:11.527 --> 00:35:13.862
Hey! Okay. look. Director.
have you lost your mind?

529
00:35:13.946 --> 00:35:16.406
It's not like
you've got some crazy budget here.

530
00:35:16.490 --> 00:35:19.034
It's a freaking indie movie.
so shoot it like one.

531
00:35:19.117 --> 00:35:21.411
Do you have any sense of balance
or what's appropriate?

532
00:35:21.495 --> 00:35:23.455
Are you that incapable
of reading the room?

533
00:35:23.539 --> 00:35:26.041
You seriously think this masterpiece
of yours is Cannes material?

534
00:35:26.124 --> 00:35:28.252
Even Bong or Park
wouldn't shoot like this.

535
00:35:29.628 --> 00:35:30.629
How would you know that?

536
00:35:30.712 --> 00:35:34.758
Don't flatter yourself. You never worked
with Bong Joon-ho or Park Chan-wook.

537
00:35:34.842 --> 00:35:36.426
What do you mean? Repeat that.

538
00:35:36.510 --> 00:35:38.053
What did you say. you little prick?

539
00:35:38.136 --> 00:35:40.014
Come here!
Say that to my face again. Seriously?

540
00:35:40.097 --> 00:35:42.724
I called you sir to show you respect
as the director. now this?

541
00:35:42.808 --> 00:35:45.143
I felt sorry for you
seeing you practically begging.

542
00:35:45.227 --> 00:35:47.688
so I've agreed
to be in your little movie without pay!

543
00:35:47.771 --> 00:35:50.357
And now...
...what the hell did you just say?

544
00:35:50.858 --> 00:35:54.098
Honestly. sir. I wouldn't have begged if
I'd known you were such a terrible actor.

545
00:35:57.865 --> 00:36:01.118
Okay. So you wanna cross the Rubicon now?

546
00:36:02.202 --> 00:36:04.663
You go ahead
and knock yourself out. you moron.

547
00:36:04.746 --> 00:36:06.123
I'm out of here. damn it!

548
00:36:14.089 --> 00:36:15.799
Cut. Let's try that again.

549
00:36:17.926 --> 00:36:19.386
-What?
-Cut. Again.

550
00:36:19.469 --> 00:36:22.222
We'll pick it up right from here.
All right. ready?

551
00:36:22.806 --> 00:36:23.974
Action!

552
00:36:25.559 --> 00:36:26.977
-<i>What?</i>
-Cut!

553
00:36:27.060 --> 00:36:28.353
All right. Ready?

554
00:36:29.146 --> 00:36:30.397
Action!

555
00:36:33.775 --> 00:36:36.361
-What?
-It's all your fault. Detective Kang!

556
00:36:36.445 --> 00:36:38.739
-Let's try that again.
-Are you kidding?

557
00:36:38.822 --> 00:36:40.157
He's freaking nuts!

558
00:37:36.213 --> 00:37:38.799
They say you can't really fix people.

559
00:37:41.051 --> 00:37:42.052
But...

560
00:37:45.013 --> 00:37:46.473
...I know I can.

561
00:37:51.520 --> 00:37:52.896
Cut! Okay!

562
00:37:54.523 --> 00:38:00.028
All right. that's a wrap on the filming of
<i>Good Detective Kang Pil-go</i>. Well done!

563
00:38:03.198 --> 00:38:05.784
-You wanna grab a beer?
-All right. Yes! Absolutely.

564
00:38:07.244 --> 00:38:09.663
All right. everybody.
fill up your glasses.

565
00:38:11.081 --> 00:38:14.084
Thank you for all your hard work
on <i>Good Detective Kang Pil-go</i>.

566
00:38:14.167 --> 00:38:17.045
Enjoy yourselves and drink up.
Come on. let's toast!

567
00:38:21.133 --> 00:38:23.802
Good shoot. good shoot.

568
00:38:23.885 --> 00:38:27.472
-All right. here's to that!
-To surviving another director from hell.

569
00:38:27.556 --> 00:38:29.057
Next time. I'm doing sound.

570
00:38:29.141 --> 00:38:32.728
Finally. it's over. right?
You can breathe now. Hyeon-jun.

571
00:38:33.603 --> 00:38:36.940
I know I've been a real pain in the ass.
I pushed too hard. said the wrong things

572
00:38:37.024 --> 00:38:38.651
and. yeah. that's on me.
I'm still learning.

573
00:38:38.734 --> 00:38:41.069
I'm an inexperienced director
trying to get it right.

574
00:38:41.153 --> 00:38:42.947
I'm sure there's a lot
you're still mad about.

575
00:38:43.030 --> 00:38:46.366
but please. please take this drink
and forget it all.

576
00:38:47.409 --> 00:38:49.119
Ah. ah. ah. ah!

577
00:38:53.790 --> 00:38:55.625
Oh!

578
00:38:57.586 --> 00:38:59.046
Oh!

579
00:38:59.588 --> 00:39:00.589
Drink up.

580
00:39:00.672 --> 00:39:03.008
Big applause
for our leading man. everyone!

581
00:39:04.718 --> 00:39:07.471
Lim Hyeon-jun! Lim Hyeon-jun!

582
00:39:07.554 --> 00:39:10.682
Lim Hyeon-jun! Lim Hyeon-jun!

583
00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:23.779
I'm gonna drink this. okay?

584
00:39:23.862 --> 00:39:25.447
Hmm.

585
00:39:26.865 --> 00:39:28.992
Whoa!

586
00:39:36.708 --> 00:39:38.710
-One more thing.
-Oh. no. here it comes.

587
00:39:38.794 --> 00:39:42.464
You little bastard! I never want
to see your freaking face again!

588
00:39:43.632 --> 00:39:45.092
And the award for Best Actor

589
00:39:45.175 --> 00:39:48.804
goes to Lim Hyeon-jun
from <i>Good Detective Kang Pil-go</i>.

590
00:39:48.887 --> 00:39:51.473
All right. let's hear
his acceptance speech now.

591
00:39:55.644 --> 00:39:59.189
Thanks to this miracle of an opportunity.
I've made my comeback.

592
00:40:00.315 --> 00:40:02.234
And I'm going to make the most of it.

593
00:40:03.527 --> 00:40:07.114
I want to continue
to be an actor for a while.

594
00:40:07.197 --> 00:40:08.406
Never forgotten.

595
00:40:12.828 --> 00:40:16.373
And I hope I can keep doing this
for many more years.

596
00:40:16.456 --> 00:40:18.667
Thank you very much! Thanks!

597
00:40:18.750 --> 00:40:21.336
{\an8}<i>And just like that.
my life completely changed overnight.</i>

598
00:40:21.419 --> 00:40:23.004
Thank you! Thank you!

599
00:40:23.088 --> 00:40:24.172
I'll do my very best.

600
00:40:24.256 --> 00:40:25.298
Thank you!

601
00:40:25.382 --> 00:40:26.383
Thank you very much.

602
00:40:28.218 --> 00:40:30.762
<i>My life. which felt like
a black-and-white documentary.</i>

603
00:40:30.846 --> 00:40:34.432
{\an8}<i>has suddenly turned into a vibrant.
colorful romantic comedy.</i>

604
00:40:34.933 --> 00:40:36.693
{\an8}GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU
CONFIRMED AS DRAMA

605
00:40:37.269 --> 00:40:38.311
24.3%

606
00:40:38.395 --> 00:40:40.438
{\an8}GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU
SEASON 2 CONFIRMED

607
00:40:40.522 --> 00:40:41.857
{\an8}26.5%

608
00:40:41.940 --> 00:40:43.817
{\an8}GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU
SEASON 3 CONFIRMED

609
00:40:43.900 --> 00:40:45.443
{\an8}27.3%

610
00:40:45.986 --> 00:40:47.196
{\an8}EVERYONE LOVES PIL-GU
AND HYEON-JUN

611
00:40:47.279 --> 00:40:48.319
{\an8}STEADY STREAM OF AD OFFERS

612
00:40:49.531 --> 00:40:50.908
{\an8}#1 MAN FANS WANT
TO SEE AGAIN: KANG PIL-GU

613
00:40:50.991 --> 00:40:52.367
{\an8}RETURNING IN SEASON 4
OF GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU

614
00:40:52.450 --> 00:40:54.536
{\an8}-JUST HOW FAR WILL IT GO?
-28.5%

615
00:41:03.962 --> 00:41:06.256
Ah...

616
00:41:07.757 --> 00:41:09.801
Oh. boy.

617
00:41:11.887 --> 00:41:13.597
-Hey!
-What the hell. man?

618
00:41:13.680 --> 00:41:14.973
You wanna take this out?

619
00:41:15.473 --> 00:41:18.643
Man. I just started it up
to see if the battery's dead. that's all.

620
00:41:18.727 --> 00:41:20.520
-Uh-huh.
-Hang on.

621
00:41:20.604 --> 00:41:22.022
Hey. I bought this with my money.

622
00:41:22.105 --> 00:41:24.149
so why can't I drive my own car
whenever I want?

623
00:41:24.232 --> 00:41:27.068
Come on. you know there are eyes
on you everywhere.

624
00:41:27.861 --> 00:41:30.322
When you have work.
just take the company car.

625
00:41:30.405 --> 00:41:32.490
This is exactly why
I need to start playing roles

626
00:41:32.574 --> 00:41:34.784
like a rich heir.
hotshot lawyer. or doctor.

627
00:41:34.868 --> 00:41:38.205
So no one will say anything
if they see me driving a car like that.

628
00:41:38.288 --> 00:41:41.124
I'm always playing broke detectives.
It's like my curse.

629
00:41:41.208 --> 00:41:44.461
No wonder everyone is shocked
when they see me in that kind of car!

630
00:41:44.544 --> 00:41:46.671
Now people don't see me as me anymore.

631
00:41:46.755 --> 00:41:48.423
I'm Detective Kang Pil-go to them.

632
00:41:48.506 --> 00:41:50.926
Sometimes. even I get confused and think

633
00:41:51.551 --> 00:41:52.969
I'm him. not Lim Hyeon-jun.

634
00:41:53.053 --> 00:41:54.429
Okay. boss. I hear ya.

635
00:41:54.512 --> 00:41:56.640
For your next project.
let's make sure it's something

636
00:41:56.723 --> 00:41:58.516
where you can really transform your image.

637
00:41:58.600 --> 00:42:01.978
Yeah. Let's please do that. Mr. Hwang.

638
00:42:03.021 --> 00:42:05.565
And don't call me "boss"
in front of people. okay?

639
00:42:07.067 --> 00:42:09.903
What? Why the hell not?
You-You love acting like my boss.

640
00:42:09.986 --> 00:42:12.906
If you call me boss.
it'll just make me look older.

641
00:42:12.989 --> 00:42:15.349
Don't you want to help your artist
improve his public image?

642
00:42:15.867 --> 00:42:18.787
Wh-What about my public image?

643
00:42:22.374 --> 00:42:25.669
Hey. sweet thang. You got a killer body.

644
00:42:25.752 --> 00:42:29.047
Let's go to my room.
I'll make sure that you get a nice tip.

645
00:42:29.130 --> 00:42:31.299
Wow. You're so hot. seriously.

646
00:42:32.968 --> 00:42:34.678
-Don't touch me. asshole.
-Asshole?

647
00:42:35.720 --> 00:42:38.723
-Get lost.
-Oh. Let's go. let's go.

648
00:42:38.807 --> 00:42:41.101
Man. they need to train
their girls better here.

649
00:42:45.105 --> 00:42:47.274
<i>Wi Jeong-sin.
36 years old.</i>

650
00:42:47.357 --> 00:42:48.817
<i>With 12 years at</i> Eunseongilbo

651
00:42:48.900 --> 00:42:50.694
<i>and a stellar track record
on the political desk.</i>

652
00:42:50.777 --> 00:42:52.153
<i>her career speaks for itself.</i>

653
00:42:53.613 --> 00:42:56.825
<i>Top of her class in Media
and Communications at Hankuk University</i>

654
00:42:56.908 --> 00:43:00.036
<i>and fluent in four languages.
English. Chinese. Arabic. and Korean.</i>

655
00:43:00.662 --> 00:43:02.205
<i>With a steel-like mentality.</i>

656
00:43:02.289 --> 00:43:05.834
<i>she managed to stay one step ahead
of the police and find crucial evidence.</i>

657
00:43:05.917 --> 00:43:08.337
<i>Even as a 20-year veteran detective
was throwing up. fainting.</i>

658
00:43:08.420 --> 00:43:10.422
<i>and breaking down
at a dismemberment scene.</i>

659
00:43:10.922 --> 00:43:13.883
<i>She climbed to the top of
a 300-foot crane to interview protestors.</i>

660
00:43:13.967 --> 00:43:15.177
<i>playing a major role in getting</i>

661
00:43:15.260 --> 00:43:18.722
<i>all unfairly dismissed contract
construction workers reinstated.</i>

662
00:43:18.805 --> 00:43:21.725
Take cover. take cover!

663
00:43:21.808 --> 00:43:23.184
<i>As a war correspondent.</i>

664
00:43:23.268 --> 00:43:27.272
<i>she was the first to report the horrors
of the Serian Civil War to the world.</i>

665
00:43:36.781 --> 00:43:39.284
<i>And she barely survived
a life-threatening operation</i>

666
00:43:39.367 --> 00:43:42.245
<i>after being hit by shrapnel
from a shell explosion.</i>

667
00:43:42.329 --> 00:43:44.205
<i>which almost cost her her leg.</i>

668
00:43:45.540 --> 00:43:48.793
<i>And that made her the youngest ever
Korean Journalist of the Year.</i>

669
00:43:48.877 --> 00:43:51.671
This year's Journalist of the Year
is Ms. Wi Jeong-sin.

670
00:43:54.049 --> 00:43:56.384
KOREAN JOURNALIST OF THE YEAR
AWARD CEREMONY

671
00:43:56.468 --> 00:43:59.304
ONNURI JOURNALISTS ASSOCIATION

672
00:44:02.474 --> 00:44:04.059
{\an8}KOREAN JOURNALIST OF THE YEAR
AWARD - WI JEONG-SIN

673
00:44:04.142 --> 00:44:05.143
{\an8}DESK CHIEF YUN HWA-YEONG

674
00:44:05.226 --> 00:44:07.479
-This report. did you write this?
-Yeah.

675
00:44:08.104 --> 00:44:09.814
What is this? A fairy tale?

676
00:44:09.898 --> 00:44:11.274
I don't buy everything. either.

677
00:44:11.358 --> 00:44:12.901
-You have to tell her!
-I don't wanna. You do it.

678
00:44:12.984 --> 00:44:15.528
But she's moving to
the entertainment desk at a sister paper.

679
00:44:15.612 --> 00:44:18.156
not even the main one. What's going on?

680
00:44:18.239 --> 00:44:19.240
What do you think?

681
00:44:19.991 --> 00:44:21.743
Someone's getting fired soon.

682
00:44:23.995 --> 00:44:25.163
Conference room now.

683
00:44:25.246 --> 00:44:26.623
-Wha... Now?
-What?

684
00:44:26.706 --> 00:44:28.083
-Oh. God.
-All right.

685
00:44:29.334 --> 00:44:30.460
See you later.

686
00:44:35.215 --> 00:44:37.592
Oh. Your new hair color looks amazing.

687
00:44:38.259 --> 00:44:39.761
Where did you get it done?

688
00:44:39.844 --> 00:44:41.596
At a salon downtown.

689
00:44:42.180 --> 00:44:43.181
Are you new?

690
00:44:44.682 --> 00:44:45.725
Not really.

691
00:44:46.684 --> 00:44:48.520
-Are you Bahn Soo-jung?
-Yeah.

692
00:44:49.938 --> 00:44:52.315
-How do you know who I am?
-You have that video. right?

693
00:44:52.399 --> 00:44:55.068
On February 20th.
you went out with those VIPs

694
00:44:55.151 --> 00:44:59.406
and shot a video. just in case
it ever turned out to be worth something.

695
00:45:01.074 --> 00:45:02.492
-Who are you?
-Well...

696
00:45:03.785 --> 00:45:04.786
a journalist.

697
00:45:06.871 --> 00:45:07.872
Chief.

698
00:45:09.332 --> 00:45:10.542
I got a scoop for you.

699
00:45:14.712 --> 00:45:17.674
28% in viewership

700
00:45:17.757 --> 00:45:21.094
and then it just kept climbing. stayed
close to 30% through all four seasons.

701
00:45:21.177 --> 00:45:23.388
-Never lost steam. Nearly 30% at its peak!
-Wow.

702
00:45:23.471 --> 00:45:27.559
-Can you believe that? 30%. 30%.
-So our production company hit it big

703
00:45:27.642 --> 00:45:29.978
with <i>Good Detective Kang Pil-go.</i>
and even bought a building.

704
00:45:30.061 --> 00:45:33.773
The networks said their
drama business wasn't profitable anymore.

705
00:45:33.857 --> 00:45:35.733
so they almost shut it down completely.

706
00:45:35.817 --> 00:45:38.069
Thanks to <i>Kang Pil-go.</i>
we were brought back to life.

707
00:45:38.153 --> 00:45:39.946
-Saved when everything seemed over.
-My gosh.

708
00:45:40.029 --> 00:45:43.116
Might sound funny coming from me.
but <i>Kang Pil-go</i> saved a lot of lives.

709
00:45:43.199 --> 00:45:44.492
Yeah. it really did!

710
00:45:44.576 --> 00:45:47.162
So you've got to keep writing dramas
like this. okay?

711
00:45:47.245 --> 00:45:51.166
Oh! Remember? <i>Country Diaries</i>?
From way back. It ran forever.

712
00:45:51.249 --> 00:45:53.043
This should run too.
like. ten. 20 years at least!

713
00:45:53.126 --> 00:45:56.588
I mean for sure. look at those
American shows like <i>CSI. NCSI</i>.

714
00:45:56.671 --> 00:45:59.591
<i>Las Vegas. Miami. New York</i>!

715
00:45:59.674 --> 00:46:03.845
If you add them all up. you can't even
count how many seasons there are!

716
00:46:03.928 --> 00:46:07.515
So. why can't we produce ten or 20 seasons
of <i>Good Detective Kang Pil-go</i>?

717
00:46:07.599 --> 00:46:09.101
-Yeah. yeah.
-You're absolutely right.

718
00:46:09.184 --> 00:46:12.437
But. you see. it's really up to
our leading man here. isn't it?

719
00:46:12.520 --> 00:46:13.688
Are you up for that?

720
00:46:23.990 --> 00:46:26.993
Are you telling me to only play
a detective until I die?

721
00:46:27.076 --> 00:46:29.496
Even Chief Gil Grissom
from <i>CSI: Las Vegas</i> stepped out

722
00:46:29.579 --> 00:46:32.582
because he wanted to try other roles!
He didn't wanna be stuck!

723
00:46:32.665 --> 00:46:34.918
Kang Pil-go is the only thing
people remember

724
00:46:35.001 --> 00:46:37.253
about my freaking acting career!

725
00:46:37.337 --> 00:46:38.588
I'm done. all right!

726
00:46:46.596 --> 00:46:48.640
Yeah. I would...

727
00:46:50.266 --> 00:46:51.726
I'd like that too. More than you know.

728
00:46:51.809 --> 00:46:53.811
-Right. right?
-I knew he'd be on board.

729
00:46:53.895 --> 00:46:55.730
Detective Kang Pil-go forever!

730
00:46:55.813 --> 00:46:58.399
No point doing some
mediocre rom-com with 2% ratings.

731
00:46:58.483 --> 00:47:01.069
-just stick with Kang Pil-go...
-Yeah. totally.

732
00:47:01.152 --> 00:47:02.153
Yeah.

733
00:47:03.780 --> 00:47:05.448
-Really no point.
-Mm-hmm.

734
00:47:06.616 --> 00:47:08.076
But I have to say...

735
00:47:08.701 --> 00:47:11.788
I've been kind of nervous
the past few weeks.

736
00:47:11.871 --> 00:47:13.790
To have a long career as an actor.

737
00:47:13.873 --> 00:47:15.833
I think it's best for <i>Kang Pil-go</i>

738
00:47:16.876 --> 00:47:18.836
to stop here.
even though I feel sad ending...

739
00:47:18.920 --> 00:47:20.881
It's because you're such
a great actor!

740
00:47:20.964 --> 00:47:23.800
I mean. you know. when an actress plays
the mistress on those morning dramas.

741
00:47:23.883 --> 00:47:26.303
people take it so seriously.
they end up slapping her on the street.

742
00:47:26.386 --> 00:47:27.387
and calling her names!

743
00:47:27.470 --> 00:47:28.930
It's a badge of honor.

744
00:47:29.013 --> 00:47:31.641
-It is a badge of honor.
-It really is. Yeah.

745
00:47:31.724 --> 00:47:32.725
Hello?

746
00:47:32.809 --> 00:47:34.936
Oh. yeah. yeah. yeah. One second.

747
00:47:35.770 --> 00:47:36.938
Oh. Right.

748
00:47:37.522 --> 00:47:39.232
Yes. Yes.

749
00:47:39.857 --> 00:47:41.150
Oh. I see.

750
00:47:48.241 --> 00:47:50.743
Uh. oh. excuse me. where's the men's room?

751
00:47:50.827 --> 00:47:52.620
-It's that way. You can't miss it.
-Oh.

752
00:47:52.704 --> 00:47:54.289
-It's that way? Thanks.
-Yes. sir.

753
00:48:06.342 --> 00:48:09.345
Shit. Why the hell is this broken?

754
00:48:27.655 --> 00:48:29.824
What if he's adamant
and refuses to do it after all?

755
00:48:29.907 --> 00:48:32.118
Right now
he only gets vague supporting roles.

756
00:48:32.201 --> 00:48:34.495
At his age who's casting him
in a rom-com or drama?

757
00:48:34.579 --> 00:48:36.831
Kang Pil-gu's all he's got.
What else can he do?

758
00:48:36.914 --> 00:48:39.584
He's probably just trying to up his rate.
so let's just play along

759
00:48:39.667 --> 00:48:41.085
and act like we're accepting it.

760
00:48:53.848 --> 00:48:56.100
Hey. yo.
Did you hear a journalist snuck in?

761
00:48:56.184 --> 00:48:58.353
A journalist? What's going on?

762
00:48:58.436 --> 00:49:01.064
-Did you see this person?
-What are the bouncers doing?

763
00:49:01.648 --> 00:49:03.191
Hey. hold on a second!

764
00:49:04.901 --> 00:49:05.943
-Hey!
-Hey!

765
00:49:36.516 --> 00:49:38.935
-What the hell are you doing?
-Uh. sorry about that!

766
00:49:39.018 --> 00:49:40.395
Please be quiet. I'll be gone in a sec.

767
00:49:40.478 --> 00:49:42.318
-Okay. This is the men's...
-I said be quiet!

768
00:49:43.815 --> 00:49:46.567
-Quiet.
-Why? What the hell's going on?

769
00:49:48.152 --> 00:49:50.697
I'm really sorry.
I'm going to step over you.

770
00:49:51.322 --> 00:49:53.491
Huh?

771
00:49:53.574 --> 00:49:54.951
My leg! My leg!

772
00:49:58.663 --> 00:50:01.124
My neck! My neck! My neck!

773
00:50:01.207 --> 00:50:02.959
Oh. God!

774
00:50:07.630 --> 00:50:10.174
Hey! My shoes! My shoes!
My shoes! My shoes!

775
00:50:10.675 --> 00:50:12.593
Quick. hurry. My shoes!

776
00:50:12.677 --> 00:50:13.761
-Here.
-Thank you.

777
00:50:13.845 --> 00:50:17.849
I'll pay for your phone.
0259-2151. Call me.

778
00:50:17.932 --> 00:50:19.308
My phone? Um.

779
00:50:20.101 --> 00:50:22.603
Oh. no! My phone!

780
00:50:22.687 --> 00:50:23.771
God damn it!

781
00:50:25.106 --> 00:50:27.024
What the hell?

782
00:50:29.193 --> 00:50:30.528
Oh. shit.

783
00:50:35.658 --> 00:50:36.659
Hey!

784
00:50:37.994 --> 00:50:39.871
There's a crazy woman wandering around.

785
00:50:39.954 --> 00:50:42.206
Just now. she walked right
into the men's room and...

786
00:50:42.999 --> 00:50:44.459
Wait. Is she a stalker?

787
00:50:44.542 --> 00:50:47.086
Anyway. she attacked me
and totally freaked me out!

788
00:50:47.170 --> 00:50:48.838
My stomach growled.
so I went to the men's room.

789
00:50:48.921 --> 00:50:50.631
then she barged in. pushed me around...

790
00:50:50.715 --> 00:50:52.508
-Ooh.
-...stepped on me.

791
00:50:53.134 --> 00:50:54.678
Next thing I know.
my phone's in the toilet...

792
00:50:54.761 --> 00:50:55.887
You're Kang Pil-go!

793
00:50:55.970 --> 00:50:57.680
Good Detective Kang Pil-go. right?

794
00:50:59.807 --> 00:51:01.517
Wow. Detective.

795
00:51:01.601 --> 00:51:03.311
Can't believe I'm meeting you here.
Big fan.

796
00:51:03.394 --> 00:51:05.354
I've seen every season. every episode.

797
00:51:06.606 --> 00:51:07.940
Ah. I appreciate that.

798
00:51:08.691 --> 00:51:10.693
So she barged in there?

799
00:51:12.069 --> 00:51:14.322
-No. she didn't. Don't worry about it.
-Oh.

800
00:51:14.989 --> 00:51:16.532
Wow. I'm with you. Kang Pil-go!

801
00:51:17.200 --> 00:51:19.118
Wow.

802
00:51:24.373 --> 00:51:26.709
<i>Right now
he only gets vague supporting roles.</i>

803
00:51:26.793 --> 00:51:28.795
At his age who's casting him
in a rom-com or drama?

804
00:51:28.878 --> 00:51:31.297
Kang Pil-gu's all he's got.
What else can he do?

805
00:51:41.057 --> 00:51:42.809
What. are you upset about something again?

806
00:51:42.892 --> 00:51:45.394
Honestly. I wouldn't have come
if I'd known it'd be like that.

807
00:51:45.478 --> 00:51:46.854
Let alone to a hostess bar.

808
00:51:46.938 --> 00:51:49.774
Yeah. I know.
That's precisely why I didn't mention it.

809
00:51:49.857 --> 00:51:50.858
About earlier...

810
00:51:51.984 --> 00:51:53.486
I'm not just saying it to make a point.

811
00:51:53.569 --> 00:51:55.947
I've had enough
of Kang Pil-go for real. all right?

812
00:51:56.030 --> 00:51:59.116
All right. I hear ya.
We can talk about that later.

813
00:51:59.909 --> 00:52:01.870
By the way. are you nervous
about the award ceremony?

814
00:52:01.953 --> 00:52:04.330
You keep popping
those calming herbal pills.

815
00:52:05.498 --> 00:52:08.251
Do I really have to go
to the award ceremony?

816
00:52:08.334 --> 00:52:10.086
It's not like I'm getting an award.

817
00:52:12.922 --> 00:52:17.635
You won one last year. didn't you?
So this year. you get to be a presenter.

818
00:52:17.718 --> 00:52:19.136
But I'm sick.

819
00:52:20.471 --> 00:52:22.765
I swear. man. I don't feel well.

820
00:52:22.849 --> 00:52:25.351
All right. Just keep popping those pills.

821
00:52:27.103 --> 00:52:30.106
<i>Baby. whoo!</i>

822
00:52:30.189 --> 00:52:31.566
<i>Baby. give me a kiss.</i>

823
00:52:32.149 --> 00:52:34.318
<i>You're such a good dancer.</i>

824
00:52:35.069 --> 00:52:37.280
<i>♪ Blown away ♪</i>

825
00:52:38.573 --> 00:52:40.074
<i>♪ In the wind... ♪</i>

826
00:52:57.341 --> 00:52:58.759
{\an8}OBTAINED HOSTESS
ENTERTAINMENT VIDEO

827
00:52:58.843 --> 00:53:00.219
{\an8}NO CIRCUMSTANTIAL EVIDENCE

828
00:53:10.021 --> 00:53:11.105
WOO YOUNG-SUK. AIDE

829
00:53:12.523 --> 00:53:14.234
<i>Are you saying
he really has nothing to do</i>

830
00:53:14.317 --> 00:53:16.402
<i>with Cheongwon City's redevelopment?</i>

831
00:53:16.485 --> 00:53:19.280
<i>That it was just his aide
who took all that money and spent it?</i>

832
00:53:19.363 --> 00:53:21.616
{\an8}<i>Woo. an aide to Congressman
Ha Gee-wan. was found dead.</i>

833
00:53:21.699 --> 00:53:24.785
{\an8}<i>Charcoal briquettes and a possible suicide
note were discovered at the scene.</i>

834
00:53:24.869 --> 00:53:27.288
<i>Even Mr. Woo's family
doesn't wanna make this a big deal.</i>

835
00:53:27.371 --> 00:53:30.374
<i>So if you keep poking around.
a lot of people are going to get hurt.</i>

836
00:53:30.458 --> 00:53:32.835
<i>I hope we have an understanding. Ms. Wi.</i>

837
00:53:56.484 --> 00:53:58.486
WOO YOUNG-SUK

838
00:54:05.034 --> 00:54:06.702
Hello. Ms. Wi. Small world.

839
00:54:07.912 --> 00:54:09.497
It's been a long time. ma'am.

840
00:54:09.580 --> 00:54:11.666
It's already been seven years.

841
00:54:11.749 --> 00:54:14.293
Ms. Wi. you don't need to come anymore.

842
00:54:15.211 --> 00:54:17.463
Thank you for
all you've done over the years.

843
00:54:19.590 --> 00:54:21.258
It's not over yet though.

844
00:54:22.051 --> 00:54:24.637
What Mr. Woo wanted to say and...

845
00:54:25.221 --> 00:54:27.682
how his death was staged as a suicide.

846
00:54:30.393 --> 00:54:32.061
I'll uncover the truth. I promise.

847
00:54:32.561 --> 00:54:33.938
EUNSEONGILBO

848
00:54:42.113 --> 00:54:43.322
My apologies. sir.

849
00:54:43.406 --> 00:54:45.658
I trust you'll
take care of that journalist.

850
00:54:45.741 --> 00:54:47.368
Yes. Understood. sir.

851
00:54:49.662 --> 00:54:50.663
<i>A sports tabloid?</i>

852
00:54:50.746 --> 00:54:53.165
-Whoa.
-What do you think that is about?

853
00:54:53.249 --> 00:54:54.917
Everyone. back to work.

854
00:54:56.043 --> 00:54:58.087
Just switch to entertainment for a year.

855
00:54:58.170 --> 00:54:59.797
Entertainment?

856
00:54:59.880 --> 00:55:02.883
Moving me to
a sports tabloid isn't just a switch.

857
00:55:02.967 --> 00:55:05.261
But. Chief. you saw the video. right?
It's a major story!

858
00:55:05.344 --> 00:55:06.971
The video barely shows the guy's face.

859
00:55:07.054 --> 00:55:09.640
and you can't even hear the voice.
How is that a story?

860
00:55:09.724 --> 00:55:12.894
All right. I totally get that you wanna
act like you didn't see or hear anything.

861
00:55:12.977 --> 00:55:15.479
But come on. Chief.
You did recognize who it was. didn't you?

862
00:55:16.188 --> 00:55:17.398
Listen.

863
00:55:17.481 --> 00:55:20.234
Do you really wanna drag us all under
with your petty ambitions?

864
00:55:20.776 --> 00:55:22.153
I have a newsroom to run!

865
00:55:22.778 --> 00:55:24.822
Do you want to see
this department wiped out?

866
00:55:24.905 --> 00:55:27.367
Did you really become a journalist
to cherry-pick for a paycheck?

867
00:55:27.450 --> 00:55:28.743
What did you just say?

868
00:55:28.826 --> 00:55:31.078
You... You've crossed the line.
How dare you?

869
00:55:31.162 --> 00:55:33.372
Oh. my gosh.

870
00:55:33.456 --> 00:55:34.874
I'm a political journalist.

871
00:55:35.791 --> 00:55:37.293
I refuse to be transferred

872
00:55:38.169 --> 00:55:39.420
and forced out against my will.

873
00:55:43.049 --> 00:55:45.509
-I don't wanna get fired.
-What a piece of work. Jesus.

874
00:55:46.010 --> 00:55:47.428
<i>Why is she transferring here?</i>

875
00:55:47.511 --> 00:55:50.556
Apparently. they've been waiting
for any chance to get rid of her.

876
00:55:50.639 --> 00:55:53.476
I hear she's a total workaholic
with zero social skills.

877
00:55:53.559 --> 00:55:55.770
A real pain to deal with.
Just a total headache.

878
00:55:55.853 --> 00:55:57.772
-Are we the bomb disposal squad now?
-God.

879
00:55:58.314 --> 00:56:01.358
That's enough. Why make such a fuss
over one person transferring here?

880
00:56:01.942 --> 00:56:05.196
After your lousy reporting today.
you should be worried about your own jobs.

881
00:56:06.447 --> 00:56:08.532
The Geumsang Arts Awards
is tonight. right?

882
00:56:09.116 --> 00:56:12.244
Find out who's wearing similar dresses
and who's dressed horribly.

883
00:56:12.328 --> 00:56:14.955
and get the story out
before the ceremony begins.

884
00:56:15.039 --> 00:56:19.085
<i>The dress war on the red carpet.
Who are the winners and losers?</i>

885
00:56:19.168 --> 00:56:22.463
<i>Two guests have just arrived
on the red carpet to kick off this event.</i>

886
00:56:22.546 --> 00:56:24.423
<i>First. the host of this award ceremony</i>

887
00:56:24.507 --> 00:56:26.300
<i>and the one
who made today's event possible.</i>

888
00:56:26.383 --> 00:56:28.135
<i>Chairman Lee Dae-ho. a young leader</i>

889
00:56:28.219 --> 00:56:29.637
-<i>guiding the industry forward.</i>
-Mr. Chairman!

890
00:56:29.720 --> 00:56:33.390
<i>Stepping onto the red carpet
with an aura that could rival any actor.</i>

891
00:56:33.474 --> 00:56:35.685
-<i>And by his side. this year's most talked...</i>
-Mr. Chairman!

892
00:56:35.768 --> 00:56:37.437
-<i>...about star...</i>
-I'm from the political desk!

893
00:56:37.520 --> 00:56:39.271
Mr. Chairman! Chairman Lee!

894
00:56:39.355 --> 00:56:41.148
<i>...a bold gown. You can feel the energy...</i>

895
00:56:41.232 --> 00:56:43.192
Excuse me. Chairman Lee!

896
00:56:43.943 --> 00:56:45.402
I'm from the political desk!

897
00:56:45.486 --> 00:56:48.030
Ooh. Mr. Chairman! Chairman Lee!

898
00:56:48.114 --> 00:56:51.742
<i>You definitely can't miss the man making
an appearance on the red carpet right now.</i>

899
00:56:51.826 --> 00:56:53.828
<i>He's the male lead
who successfully led the drama</i>

900
00:56:53.911 --> 00:56:56.747
Good Detective Kang Pil-go
<i>all the way through to season four.</i>

901
00:56:56.831 --> 00:56:59.459
<i>And the winner of last year's grand prize
at the Geumsang Arts Awards</i>

902
00:56:59.542 --> 00:57:02.169
<i>in the drama category for Best Actor.
And now the...</i>

903
00:57:02.253 --> 00:57:05.756
Mr. Chairman! Can you please comment
on the retaliatory personnel decisions

904
00:57:05.840 --> 00:57:07.925
taking place at <i>Eunseongilbo</i>?

905
00:57:08.008 --> 00:57:10.803
-Where did you say you're from?
-I'm Wi Jeong-sin from <i>Eunseongilbo</i>!

906
00:57:10.886 --> 00:57:12.388
You've ignored my calls
and meeting requests.

907
00:57:12.471 --> 00:57:14.557
so I had no choice
but to come here myself!

908
00:57:14.640 --> 00:57:15.975
-Let's talk later. okay?
-Mr. Chairman!

909
00:57:16.058 --> 00:57:18.018
Please cancel my transfer!

910
00:57:18.102 --> 00:57:19.353
We'll talk later.

911
00:57:20.312 --> 00:57:22.439
Sorry. Move. please.

912
00:58:13.782 --> 00:58:14.992
Hyeon-jun!

913
00:59:22.810 --> 00:59:25.187
{\an8}SPECIAL THANKS TO OH YEON-SEO
FOR HER GUEST APPEARANCE

914
00:59:28.232 --> 00:59:30.317
{\an8}<i>How can I be sane after all that?</i>

915
00:59:30.401 --> 00:59:32.319
{\an8}<i>You must have
a terrible memory.</i>

916
00:59:32.403 --> 00:59:34.488
{\an8}We've met twice before.
Two very dramatic encounters.

917
00:59:34.571 --> 00:59:38.075
{\an8}<i>There's no way
this woman is a journalist.</i>

918
00:59:38.158 --> 00:59:39.744
{\an8}You can't just mess
with the press like that!

919
00:59:39.827 --> 00:59:41.870
{\an8}-Do you want to bury Lim Hyeon-jun?
-Yes!

920
00:59:41.954 --> 00:59:45.082
{\an8}<i>Everyone has their dirty laundry.
and where there's smoke. there's fire.</i>

921
00:59:45.165 --> 00:59:47.876
{\an8}<i>Ms. Wi. I'm very sorry
but I will have to ask you to leave.</i>

922
00:59:47.960 --> 00:59:50.921
{\an8}<i>She should be apologizing
to me on her knees. if anything!</i>

923
00:59:51.005 --> 00:59:52.673
{\an8}<i>I just wanna give him
the same in return.</i>

924
00:59:52.756 --> 00:59:55.384
{\an8}Come on. is this journalist
actually crazy or what?

924
00:59:56.305 --> 01:00:56.639
